Registration - A separate Registration Form must be executed by each registrant and submitted in one copy. A Registration Form in behalf of a child under 14 years of age shall be executed by the parent of guardian. Public reporting burden for this collection of information is estimated to average 35 minutes per response. If you have comments regarding the accuracy of this estimate or suggestions for simplifying this form, you can write to both the U.S. Department of Justice, Immigration and Naturalization Service Policy Directives and Instructions Branch (HQPDIB), Washington, D.C. 20536 and to the Office of Management and Budget, Paperwork Reduction Project: OMB No. 1115-0057, Washington, D.C. 20503. *U.S. GPO: 1993-342-483/72355
